PATCH: Fix UPC-A code length validation
Corrected the condition in the UPC-A code generation in ShopProducts model. The previous check was for exact length of 12 digits but the adjusted condition now correctly checks if the UPC-A code length exceeds 12 digits, in line with UPC-A standard. This will prevent invalid codes from passing the validation.

PATCH: Refactor and standardize UPC-A code generation
Adjusted and standardized the method for generating UPC-A codes in the ShopProducts model. The number of digits used now correctly aligns with the UPC-A standard of 12 digits, including a precise checksum calculation. Simultaneously, exceptions have been added to handle error scenarios such as a missing Product ID or invalid UPC-A code length.

PATCH: Extend UPC6A generation from 11 to 12 digits in ShopProducts model
The calculateUPCA method in ShopProducts model has been adjusted to expand the number of digits from 11 to 12. This modification not only aligns the UPCA generation method to the standard UPC-A format, but also adjusts the loop range for checksum calculation, ensuring accurate barcode generation.

PATCH: Change barcode type from EAN-13 to UPC-A in 'product' route
Updated the barcode generation method in '/product' route. EAN-13 type has been replaced with UPC-A. This change was prompted to synchronize the barcode generation method across the application, specifically in ShopProducts model and ShopProductEdit screen. Adjusted checksum digit calculation accordingly.

PATCH: Update barcode generation from EAN-13 to UPC-A
The method for barcode generation in ShopProducts model has been updated. Instead of generating an EAN-13 barcode, it now generates a UPC-A barcode based on the product's ID. This change also affects the ShopProductEdit screen, which now uses the new UPC-A generation method. The checksum digit calculation has been adjusted to match the changes in barcode generation.
